  "prompt": "How do I increase font size in Quora?",
  "response": "To increase the font size on Quora, you can adjust your browser's settings or use specific keyboard shortcuts. Here are a few methods:\n\n1. **Browser Zoom:**\n   - **Windows:** Press `Ctrl` and `+` to zoom in (increase font size) and `Ctrl` and `-` to zoom out.\n   - **Mac:** Press `Command` and `+` to zoom in and `Command` and `-` to zoom out.\n\n2. **Browser Settings:**\n   - Most browsers have settings where you can change the default font size. You can access these settings through the menu (typically under \"Settings\" or \"Preferences\"), then look for \"Appearance\" or \"Fonts.\"\n\n3. **Custom CSS:**\n   - If you're knowledgeable about web development, you can use browser extensions that allow you to apply custom CSS to any website, including Quora.\n\n4. **Accessibility Options:**\n   - Operating systems often provide accessibility settings that allow you to increase text size across applications, including web browsers.\n\nThese methods should help you view texts on Quora in a larger font. Keep in mind that increasing font size through zoom will affect the entire page layout.",
